    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-25T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-25T06:00:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.75/14: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Goold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-25T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 25, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 25—10:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. Your telegram No. 26, May 18, 6 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d105fn32">Not
                        printed.</note> An adjudication for the telephone concession is to be held
                    on June 5th. Minister of Communications has indicated that he would like local
                    agent to make firm<note n="33" xml:id="d105fn33">i. e., the International
                        Telephone and Telegraph Corporation.</note> offer, although company’s ideas
                    have been altogether different from those of government. Local agent has
                    telegraphed to London requesting that authorized agent be sent at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Goold</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
